<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title><%= pageTitle %> | MyTaxCalcs</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Use the free tax refund calculator to estimate your federal refund or amount owed based on income, deductions, credits, withholding, and estimated payments.">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

  <meta name="google-site-verification" content="TT2j7SglafccBK-Nfk4l1XVIDXEJdSmyQJf2wL9QY0o" />

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">

  <script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-5193834725888549"
     crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>
<body>
  <header class="small-header">
    <nav class="nav">
      <a href="/" class="logo">
        <span class="logo-icon">💵</span>
        <span>MyTaxCalcs</span>
      </a>

      <div class="nav-links">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/income-tax-calculator">Income Tax</a>
        <a href="/tax-refund-calculator">Tax Refund</a>
        <a href="/self-employment-tax-calculator">Self-Employment</a>
        <a href="/capital-gains-tax-calculator">Capital Gains</a>
        <a href="/sales-tax-calculator">Sales Tax</a>
        <a href="/about">About</a>
      </div>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main class="container two-column">
    <section class="card">
      <h1>Tax Refund Calculator</h1>
      <p>Estimate whether you may receive a federal tax refund or owe additional federal tax.</p>

      <form method="POST" action="/tax-refund-calculator" class="form">
        <label>
          Gross annual income
          <input type="number" name="grossIncome" value="<%= form.grossIncome || '' %>" placeholder="85000" min="0" step="0.01" required>
        </label>

        <label>
          Filing status
          <select name="filingStatus">
            <option value="single" <%= form.filingStatus === "single" ? "selected" : "" %>>Single</option>
            <option value="marriedJoint" <%= form.filingStatus === "marriedJoint" ? "selected" : "" %>>Married Filing Jointly</option>
            <option value="marriedSeparate" <%= form.filingStatus === "marriedSeparate" ? "selected" : "" %>>Married Filing Separately</option>
            <option value="headHousehold" <%= form.filingStatus === "headHousehold" ? "selected" : "" %>>Head of Household</option>
          </select>
        </label>

        <label>
          Deduction type
          <select name="deductionType">
            <option value="standard" <%= !form.deductionType || form.deductionType === "standard" ? "selected" : "" %>>Standard deduction</option>
            <option value="itemized" <%= form.deductionType === "itemized" ? "selected" : "" %>>Itemized deduction</option>
          </select>
        </label>

        <label>
          Itemized deduction amount
          <input type="number" name="itemizedDeduction" value="<%= form.itemizedDeduction || '' %>" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01">
        </label>

        <label>
          Federal tax withheld
          <input type="number" name="federalWithheld" value="<%= form.federalWithheld || '' %>" placeholder="12000" min="0" step="0.01">
        </label>

        <label>
          Estimated tax payments
          <input type="number" name="estimatedPayments" value="<%= form.estimatedPayments || '' %>" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01">
        </label>

        <label>
          Other tax payments
          <input type="number" name="otherPayments" value="<%= form.otherPayments || '' %>" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01">
        </label>

        <label>
          Non-refundable tax credits
          <input type="number" name="nonRefundableCredits" value="<%= form.nonRefundableCredits || '' %>" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01">
        </label>

        <label>
          Refundable tax credits
          <input type="number" name="refundableCredits" value="<%= form.refundableCredits || '' %>" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01">
        </label>

        <button type="submit">Calculate Refund Estimate</button>
      </form>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>Estimated Results</h2>

      <% if (!result) { %>
        <p class="muted">Enter your income, withholding, payments, and credits to estimate your refund or amount owed.</p>
      <% } else { %>
        <div class="results">
          <p><span>Tax year:</span> <strong><%= result.taxYear %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Gross income:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.grossIncome).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Deduction:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.deduction).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Taxable income:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.taxableIncome).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Federal tax before credits:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.federalTaxBeforeCredits).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Non-refundable credits:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.nonRefundableCredits).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Tax after non-refundable credits:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.federalTaxAfterNonRefundableCredits).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Federal tax withheld:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.federalWithheld).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Estimated tax payments:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.estimatedPayments).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Other payments:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.otherPayments).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Refundable credits:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.refundableCredits).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Total payments and refundable credits:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.totalPayments).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>

          <% if (result.refundOrOwed >= 0) { %>
            <p><span>Estimated refund:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.refundOrOwed).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <% } else { %>
            <p><span>Estimated amount owed:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.abs(Math.round(result.refundOrOwed)).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <% } %>

          <p><span>Effective tax rate:</span> <strong><%= (result.effectiveTaxRate * 100).toFixed(1) %>%</strong></p>
          <p><span>Marginal tax rate:</span> <strong><%= (result.marginalRate * 100).toFixed(1) %>%</strong></p>
        </div>
      <% } %>

      <p class="disclaimer">Estimate only. Not tax, legal, accounting, or financial advice.</p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <section class="container content seo-content">
    <p class="eyebrow dark">Tax Refund Guide</p>
    <h2>How this tax refund calculator works</h2>
    <p>
      This tax refund calculator estimates whether you may receive a federal refund or owe
      additional tax by comparing your estimated federal tax liability with your withholding,
      estimated payments, other payments, and refundable credits.
    </p>

    <div class="seo-grid">
      <div class="seo-mini-card">
        <h3>Refund estimate</h3>
        <p>
          A refund may occur when total tax payments and refundable credits are greater than
          your estimated federal tax after non-refundable credits.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="seo-mini-card">
        <h3>Amount owed estimate</h3>
        <p>
          You may owe additional tax if your estimated federal tax is greater than your withholding,
          estimated payments, other payments, and refundable credits.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="seo-mini-card">
        <h3>Credits and payments</h3>
        <p>
          Non-refundable credits can reduce your tax to zero. Refundable credits and payments can
          increase your refund estimate.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Tax refund FAQ</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is a tax refund?</h3>
        <p>
          A tax refund is money returned to you when your tax payments and refundable credits are
          greater than your final tax liability.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Why might I owe taxes instead of getting a refund?</h3>
        <p>
          You may owe taxes if not enough was withheld from your paycheck, if you had self-employment
          income, investment income, fewer credits, or other taxable income without enough payments.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is the difference between non-refundable and refundable credits?</h3>
        <p>
          A non-refundable credit can reduce your tax liability, but generally does not create a refund
          by itself. A refundable credit may increase your refund even if your tax is already zero.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Does this calculator include state refunds?</h3>
        <p>
          No. This calculator focuses on federal refund estimates. State tax refunds depend on each
          state’s tax rules, withholding, credits, and filing requirements.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can I use this to file my taxes?</h3>
        <p>
          No. This calculator is for educational estimates only. For filing, use official tax forms,
          tax software, or a qualified tax professional.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: April 2026</p>
  </section>

 <section class="container content related-calculators">
  <p class="eyebrow dark">Related Calculators</p>
  <h2>More tax calculators</h2>

  <div class="related-grid">
    <a href="/income-tax-calculator">Income Tax Calculator</a>
    <a href="/tax-refund-calculator">Tax Refund Calculator</a>
    <a href="/self-employment-tax-calculator">Self-Employment Tax Calculator</a>
